@Analytics_BE_HostAddress = http://localhost:5126

### Login User
# @name login
POST {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "dev@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!"
}

###

### Variable Assignment from Login Response
# IMPORTANT: Click "Send Request" on the 'Login User' request above FIRST to populate this variable.
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

### Get Current User (Me)
GET {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### Users CRUD - Get All
GET {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### Departments CRUD - Get All
GET {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/departments
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### Roles CRUD - Get All
GET {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/roles
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### Job Titles CRUD - Get All
GET {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/jobtitles
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### User Groups CRUD - Get All
GET {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/usergroups
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### Create Department Example
POST {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/departments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
    "name": "Engineering",
    "description": "Technical and software development",
    "code": "ENG",
    "isActive": true
}

###

### Register User (For testing new signups)
POST {{Analytics_BE_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "New Developer",
    "email": "dev@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!",
    "role": "user"
}
